tackers to conduct a ReDoS (Regular expression Denial of Service) attack via a Subversion repository with crafted info data, because the InfoSvnCommand argument is mishandled."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve202242969","id":"CVE-2022-42969 (sca)","description":"The py library for Python allows remote attackers to conduct a ReDoS (Regular expression Denial of Service) attack via a Subversion repository with crafted info data, because the InfoSvnCommand argument is mishandled.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"Curl-Auth-Header - 9dcbb621-11db-4eac-a1ee-a945edba3438 (sscs-secret-detection)","name":"Curl-Auth-Header","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"Remove curl-auth-header secr*** from source control and store it in your organization’s secret manager (e.g., AWS Secrets Manager, Azure Key Vault, HashiCorp Vault).","markdown":"Remove curl-auth-header secr*** from source control and store it in your organization’s secret manager (e.g., AWS Secrets Manager, Azure Key Vault, HashiCorp Vault)."},"fullDescription":{"text":"Discovered a potential authorization token provided in a curl command header, which could compromise the curl accessed resource."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Curl-Auth-Header","id":"Curl-Auth-Header - 9dcbb621-11db-4eac-a1ee-a945edba3438 (sscs-secret-detection)","description":"Discovered a potential authorization token provided in a curl command header, which could compromise the curl accessed resource.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sscs-secret-detection"]}},{"id":"Privilege Escalation Allowed - 5572cc5e-1e4c-4113-92a6-7a8a3bd25e6d [Taken from query_id] (kics)","name":"Privilege Escalation Allowed","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"Containers should not run with allowPrivilegeEscalation in order to prevent them from gaining more privileges than their parent process Value: metadata.name={{ubuntu-dev}}.spec.template.spec.containers.name={{ubuntu}}.securityContext.allowPrivilegeEscalation is undefined Excepted value: metadata.name={{ubuntu-dev}}.spec.template.spec.containers.name={{ubuntu}}.securityContext.allowPrivilegeEscalation should be set and should be set to false","markdown":"Containers should not run with allowPrivilegeEscalation in order to prevent them from gaining more privileges than their parent process \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eValue:\u003c/strong\u003e metadata.name={{ubuntu-dev}}.spec.template.spec.containers.name={{ubuntu}}.securityContext.allowPrivilegeEscalation is undefined \u003cbr\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eExcepted value:\u003c/strong\u003e metadata.name={{ubuntu-dev}}.spec.template.spec.containers.name={{ubuntu}}.securityContext.allowPrivilegeEscalation should be set and should be set to false"},"fullDescription":{"text":"Containers should not run with allowPrivilegeEscalation in order to prevent them from gaining more privileges than their parent process Value: metadata.name={{ubuntu-dev}}.spec.template.spec.containers.name={{ubuntu}}.securityContext.allowPrivilegeEscalation is undefined Excepted value: metadata.name={{ubuntu-dev}}.spec.template.spec.containers.name={{ubuntu}}.securityContext.allowPrivilegeEscalation should be set and should be set to false"},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Privilege Escalation Allowed","id":"Privilege Escalation Allowed - 5572cc5e-1e4c-4113-92a6-7a8a3bd25e6d [Taken from query_id] (kics)","description":"Containers should not run with allowPrivilegeEscalation in order to prevent them from gaining more privileges than their parent process Value: metadata.name={{ubuntu-dev}}.spec.template.spec.containers.name={{ubuntu}}.securityContext.allowPrivilegeEscalation is undefined Excepted value: metadata.name={{ubuntu-dev}}.spec.template.spec.containers.name={{ubuntu}}.securityContext.allowPrivilegeEscalation should be set and should be set to false","tags":["security","checkmarx","kics"]}},{"id":"Cxdca8e59f-8bfe (sca)","name":"Cxdca8e59f8bfe","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"In NPM `inflight` there is a Memory Leak because some resources are not freed correctly after being used. It appears to affect all versions, as the issue was not addressed and no fix is found. NOTE: In the meantime, `logdna-agent`, a package that depends on `inflight`, has merged a commit to address this solely in their package (so it should be fixed in `logdna-agent` in versions 1.6.5 and later). `Node-glob`, a package that also depends on `inflight`, was also planning to address this by not using `inflight` after version 8 is released, but it is still being used.","markdown":"In NPM `inflight` there is a Memory Leak because some resources are not freed correctly after being used. It appears to affect all versions, as the issue was not addressed and no fix is found. NOTE: In the meantime, `logdna-agent`, a package that depends on `inflight`, has merged a commit to address this solely in their package (so it should be fixed in `logdna-agent` in versions 1.6.5 and later). `Node-glob`, a package that also depends on `inflight`, was also planning to address this by not using `inflight` after version 8 is released, but it is still being used."},"fullDescription":{"text":"In NPM `inflight` there is a Memory Leak because some resources are not freed correctly after being used. It appears to affect all versions, as the issue was not addressed and no fix is found. NOTE: In the meantime, `logdna-agent`, a package that depends on `inflight`, has merged a commit to address this solely in their package (so it should be fixed in `logdna-agent` in versions 1.6.5 and later). `Node-glob`, a package that also depends on `inflight`, was also planning to address this by not using `inflight` after version 8 is released, but it is still being used."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cxdca8e59f8bfe","id":"Cxdca8e59f-8bfe (sca)","description":"In NPM `inflight` there is a Memory Leak because some resources are not freed correctly after being used. It appears to affect all versions, as the issue was not addressed and no fix is found. NOTE: In the meantime, `logdna-agent`, a package that depends on `inflight`, has merged a commit to address this solely in their package (so it should be fixed in `logdna-agent` in versions 1.6.5 and later). `Node-glob`, a package that also depends on `inflight`, was also planning to address this by not using `inflight` after version 8 is released, but it is still being used.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"Using Unrecommended Namespace - 611ab018-c4aa-4ba2-b0f6-a448337509a6 [Taken from query_id] (kics)","name":"Using Unrecommended Namespace","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"Namespaces like \u0026#39;default\u0026#39;, \u0026#39;kube-system\u0026#39; or \u0026#39;kube-public\u0026#39; should not be used Value: 'metadata.namespace' is set to default Excepted value: 'metadata.namespace' should not be set to default, kube-system or kube-public","markdown":"Namespaces like \u0026#39;default\u0026#39;, \u0026#39;kube-system\u0026#39; or \u0026#39;kube-public\u0026#39; should not be used \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eValue:\u003c/strong\u003e 'metadata.namespace' is set to default \u003cbr\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eExcepted value:\u003c/strong\u003e 'metadata.namespace' should not be set to default, kube-system or kube-public"},"fullDescription":{"text":"Namespaces like \u0026#39;default\u0026#39;, \u0026#39;kube-system\u0026#39; or \u0026#39;kube-public\u0026#39; should not be used Value: 'metadata.namespace' is set to default Excepted value: 'metadata.namespace' should not be set to default, kube-system or kube-public"},"properties":{"security-severity":"4.0","name":"Using Unrecommended Namespace","id":"Using Unrec